Title: Priors, Posterior Odds and Lagrange Multiplier Statistics in Bayesian Analyses of Cointegration  
Author: Frank Kleibergen Richard Paap 
Keyword: cointegration, Bayesian analysis, Lagrange multiplier statistics, Bayes factors.  
Address: Rotterdam, P.O. Box 1738, NL-3000 DR Rotterdam, The Netherlands,  
Affiliation: Econometric Institute, Erasmus University  
Note: Corresponding author:  
Email: e-mail: kleibergen@few.eur.nl.  
Date: February 17, 1997  
Abstract: Using the standard linear error correction model as a base, a unified theory of Bayesian analyses of cointegration models is constructed. This is achieved by defining (natural conjugate) priors in the linear error correction model and using the implied priors for the cointegration model. Using these priors, posterior results for the cointegration model are obtained using Metropolis-Hastings samplers. For coin-tegration rank determination we use both Bayesian Lagrange multiplier statistics and posterior odds ratios/Bayes factors. The Bayes factors show close resemblance with the posterior information criterium of Phillips and Ploberger (1996). Two different decompositions of the long run multiplier to reflect cointegration are used. The first allows for the analytical construction of some conditional posteriors, but is sensitive to the ordering of the variables. The second is invariant to the ordering but does not lead to analytical expressions of conditional posteriors. To show the applicability of the derived theory, the constructed procedures are applied to the UK data of Hendry and Doornik (1994) and the Danish data of Johansen and Juselius (1990) and a few simulated series. y Tinbergen Institute, Erasmus University Rotterdam, P.O. Box 1738, NL-3000 DR Rotterdam, The Netherlands, e-mail: paap@tir.few.eur.nl. Both authors thank the Netherlands Foundation for Scientific Research (N.W.O.) for their financial support. Comments from the participants of the 1996 world meeting of ISBA in Cape Town, South Africa, are gratefully acknowledged. Paper also available at: http://www.eur.nl/few/ei/faculty/kleibergen 
